{
  "local_port": 34398,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How can I record video with Drift Ghost-S while charging?",
  "response": "Recording video with your Drift Ghost-S while it's charging is a great way to extend your recording sessions without worrying about battery life. Here's a step-by-step guide to help you achieve this:\n\n1. **Verify Compatibility:**\n   - **Check the User Manual:** Ensure that the Drift Ghost-S supports pass-through charging (charging while recording). Some cameras are designed to handle this, while others might not.\n   - **Firmware Update:** Make sure your camera's firmware is up to date. Manufacturers often release updates that improve functionality, including charging capabilities.\n\n2. **Select the Right Cable:**\n   - **Use the Original Cable:** It's best to use the USB cable that came with your Drift Ghost-S. This ensures compatibility and optimal power delivery.\n   - **Quality Matters:** If you need a replacement, choose a high-quality cable that supports both power and data transfer. Poor-quality cables can lead to insufficient charging or data interruptions.\n\n3. **Choose an Appropriate Power Source:**\n   - **Wall Adapter:** Using a wall charger (like a USB wall adapter) is preferable over a computer USB port. Wall adapters typically provide a more stable and higher power output, reducing the risk of the camera draining the power while recording.\n   - **Power Bank:** If you're outdoors or away from power outlets, a high-capacity power bank can be a reliable alternative. Ensure the power bank supports the necessary output for your camera.\n\n4. **Connect and Configure:**\n   - **Plug In While Recording:** Connect your Drift Ghost-S to the power source using the appropriate cable while it's turned on and set to record.\n   - **Monitor Battery and Heat:** Continuously recording while charging can generate additional heat. Keep an eye on the camera to ensure it doesn't overheat, especially in hot environments.\n\n5. **Optimize Camera Settings:**\n   - **Resolution and Frame Rate:** Higher resolutions and frame rates consume more power. If possible, adjust these settings to balance video quality and battery consumption.\n   - **Power-Saving Modes:** Enable any available power-saving features to extend the recording time while charging.\n\n6. **Use External Accessories If Needed:**\n   - **Charging Adapters:** Some third-party accessories are designed to facilitate charging while recording. Ensure they are compatible with the Drift Ghost-S and meet safety standards.\n   - **Mounting Solutions:** If you're using the camera in motion (like on a vehicle), ensure that the charging setup doesn't interfere with the camera's mounting and that cables are secured to prevent entanglement.\n\n7. **Troubleshooting Tips:**\n   - **No Charging While Recording:** If the camera doesn't charge while recording, double-check the cable and power source. Some cables might only support charging or data transfer, not both simultaneously.\n   - **Intermittent Recording:** Ensure that the power source provides a consistent output. Fluctuations can cause the camera to stop recording intermittently.\n\n8. **Consult Customer Support:**\n   - If you've followed all the steps and still encounter issues, reach out to Drift\u2019s customer support. They can provide specific advice or inform you if there are any known issues with pass-through charging on your model.\n\n**Safety Precautions:**\n- **Avoid Overheating:** Prolonged charging and recording can generate heat. Ensure the camera is placed in a well-ventilated area.\n- **Use Certified Accessories:** Always use certified cables and power sources to prevent damage to your camera or potential safety hazards.\n\nBy following these guidelines, you should be able to successfully record videos with your Drift Ghost-S while it's charging, ensuring longer recording times and uninterrupted action capture.",
